<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>The Freedom Server - Sleaze, Magazine of Politics</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#fdfaff"></HEAD><BODY><HR NOSHADE><H1><CENTER>The Freedom Server&copy;</CENTER></H1><H3><CENTER>Second Edition</CENTER></H3><HR noshade><H2><CENTER>Sleaze</CENTER></H2><H3><CENTER>The Magazine of Politics. </CENTER></H3><H4><CENTER>1996, March </CENTER></H4><P><CENTER><HR noshade><BR><BR>This page has been visited <BR><BR><IMG SRC="/cgi-bin/Counter.cgi?www.freedom-server.co.uk.Sleaze-Mar.html" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <BR><BR>since 1996, May 4. <BR></CENTER><P><HR noshade><TT>Created: 1995, August 1<BR>Revised: 1996, June 1<BR>Version: 002i </TT><HR><H4><CENTER>| <A HREF="index.html">Home</A> | <A HREF="Contents.html">Tableof Contents</A> | </CENTER></H4><HR NOSHADE><BR><BR>Your politicians--and the hard-earned money they have taken from you--inaction. <BR><BR>This publication covers all departments of politics: Civil, Military, andReligious. <BR><BR>The main objective of aspiring politicians is to get elected. Then, onceelected and having descended* to political office, the main objective isto be re-elected. To ensure achieving this objective, they will do virtuallyanything, as illustrated in this section. <BR><UL>* Descending to political office <B>is</B> the correct direction, sincevirtually all political activites are immoral. (See the <A HREF="Glossary.html">Glossaryof Terms</A> for definitions). <BR><BR>A politician can only be said to have &quot;ascended&quot; to a positionwhen they are no longer in a position to control the property and livesof others without the consent of the victim(s). <BR></UL>Trading people, places, and things for votes. Their main objective is toremain in power--in control of other people's lives and money. The exhilarationof people kowtowing to you, and the knowledge that others are looking enviouslyat this process. The endless &quot;photo opportunities&quot; to enhanceone's position of power. The arriving, waiting, and departing limousines.The helicopters to make sure one is not caught in the traffic lesser mortalsare subject to, and which the politicians are unable to solve. (A dilutedand imparied form of socialist-capitalism is able to build more cars thanpoliticians can provide roads for.) <BR><BR>It is not so much the &quot;sleaze&quot; of politics that is significant,but rather the emptiness of the concept of one person or group of personscontrolling the lives and destiny of others through the mechanism of coercion.Even in the so-called &quot;democratic&quot; societies in which people supposedlygive their consent to this coercive process. Mainly, I believe, because&quot;it has always been this way,&quot; and because there seems not otherway for volitional societies to operate, which is of course not true. <BR><BR>Such coercive systems violate a basic law of nature regarding the behaviorof volitional beings which states that all concepts of happiness pursuedby <B>moral</B> means are equally valid. A corollary might be that any attemptby one individual to interfere in this process and the life of another personis of course immoral, and it should be obvious that it is counter-productiveand leads to disorder in a society. <BR><BR>Do you want someone else's idea of happiness substituted for yours? Do youwant their idea of happiness imposed on you? Is it realistic that groupsof people should have the same idea or concept imposed upon them? Forgettingfor the moment that such a thing is in any case immoral. <BR><BR>The word &quot;sleaze&quot; is often used to indicate corruption. But itshould be remembered that corruption can not exist unless one party to arelationship has an accepted and &quot;authorized&quot; (legal, in politicalsocieties) ability to control the lives and properties of others withouttheir permission. Without this access to the monopoly on police powers whicha political state encompasses the concept of corruption loses all its meaning.<BR><BR><HR NOSHADE><H3><CENTER>Sleaze for 1966, the Month of March</CENTER></H3><HR NOSHADE><TABLE border> <TR> <TH>Information Source</TH> <TH>PoliticalAction or Event</TH> <TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>SundayTimes (London)</B><BR>1996, March 3<BR>&quot;Clinton declares emergency over anti-Cuba protest&quot;<BR>p. 1-18 </TD> <TD> <BR><BR>The &quot;Commander in Chief&quot; and Chief Draft Dodger has declared a&quot;National Emergency&quot; over Cuba's shooting down of two US privateaircraft. <BR><BR>He is also proposing a new law regarding property expropriated by Castroafter his rebellion against the previous Ruler, Battista. This law willhave disastrous consequences for US and British companies doing businessin Cuba. <BR><BR>However, the American Ruler--Clinton--has the authority to delay implementationof the law for six months, which he will do so as to be able to obtain thevote of Cuban-Americans in Florida. This being crucial to his re-election.<BR><BR></TD> <TD> <BR><BR>Is this, or is this not a bribe? <BR><BR>Of course it is, but not if you are spart of the Political R&eacute;gime,where it is only considered &quot;politics.&quot; <BR><BR></TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> </TABLE> <TABLE border><TR> <TH>Information Source</TH> <TH>Political Action or Event</TH> <TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH></TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <HR NOSHADE><P><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>] </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD		Reality		</td> </TR> </TABLE> <HR NOSHADE><P><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>] </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><TABLE border> <TR> <TH>Information Source</TH> <TH>PoliticalAction or Event</TH> <TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> </TABLE> <HR NOSHADE><P><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>] </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><TABLE border> <TR> <TH>Information Source</TH> <TH>PoliticalAction or Event</TH> <TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD		Reality		</tr> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TR> </TABLE> <HR NOSHADE><P><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>] </CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><TABLE border> <TR> <TH>Information Source</TH> <TH>PoliticalAction or Event</TH> <TH>Translation/Reality/Comment</TH> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<BR>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><B>Publication</B><BR>Date<BR>Title<P><CENTER>p. nn </TD> <TD> Politics </TD> <TD> Reality </TD> </TR> </TABLE><HR NOSHADE><center>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>]</center><HR NOSHADE><BR><center>&copy;1995 - The Universal Salvage Corporation <BR><BR><I>Specialists in Dying Civilizations</I> <BR></CENTER><P><HR NOSHADE><B>Contact Information:</B><BR>E-Mail: administrator@Freedom-Server.co.uk<BR><HR>The URL of this page is: <BR><P><CENTER>&lt;http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Sleaze-Mar.html&gt; <HR NOSHADE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
