ild five.		<a href="#19r">Return</a><p><a name="20"><li> Jim Sherman, "Nightmare on Bagby," Public News,	March 17. 1993, p. 5.		<a href="#20r">Return</a><p><a name="21"><li>Bill Gilmer. "Zoning Rejected Agun: Why the Issue	Won't Die," Houston Business: A Perspective on the Economy, November,	1993, p. 2.		<a href="#21r">Return</a><p><a name="22"><li>Lisa Delany. "The Expediters: They Get You Through	Austin City Hall," The Austin Business Journal, February 3. 1986, p.	I5. Even in pro-growth Dallas, zoning slows large development	projects by 4-8 months. See Richard B. Peiser, "Land Development	Regulation: A Case Study of Dallas and Houston, Texas," American Real	Estate and Economics Journal, 9 (Winter 1981), pp. 397-417.		<a href="#22r">Return</a><p><a name="23"><li>Houston Zoning Ordinance, 48-2112 (e), I-5.	<a href="#23r">Return</a><p><a name="24"><li>Joanne H. Pratt, "Home-Based Work: New Opportunities	for Women?" The Freeman, May 1988, p. 198.		<a href="#24r">Return</a><p><a name="25"><li>"HHA board studies home-based businesses,"	Neighborhood News, Summer, 1992, p. 4.		<a href="#25r">Return</a><p><a name="26"><li>Carl Hooper, "Silver lining likely in city job	market," The Houston Post, June 18, 1992, p. E-1.		<a href="#26r">Return</a><p><a name="27"><li>Jim Sherman, "Dear Mr. Litke, An Open Letter to Bob	Litke, Deputy Director of Planning and Development," The Houston	Agenda, June, 1993, p. 4.		<a href="#27r">Return</a><p><a name="28"><li>Jack Harris, "Understanding Land-Use Controls,"	Texas Real Estate Research Center technical report, July 1986,	p. 21.		<a href="#28r">Return</a><p><a name="29"><li>Mark Kaufman, "An architect 'insider' speaks out	against zoning," The Houston Business Journal, March 29, 1993,	p. 8.		<a href="#29r">Return</a><p><a name="30"><li>Herman Lauhoff, "Without zoning, American dream is a	'Houston nightmare'," The Houston Chronicle, August 12, 1990, D. 5E.		<a href="#30r">Retur