<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>The Freedom Server-Cat License or Death</TITLE>	<META Name="AU" CONTENT="William W. Morgan">		<META HTTP-EQUIV="KEYWORDS"		CONTENT="Galambos, government, coercion, capitalism, 			history, Bedeman, capital punishment">			<META HTTP-EQUIV="Reply-to"		CONTENT="administrator@freedom-server.co.uk"></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><hr noshade><center><H1>The Freedom Server&copy;</H1><H3>Second Edition</H3><hr noshade><h4>| <a href="index.html">Home</a> | <a href="Contents.html">Table of Contents</a> | </h4><h4>| <a href="Essays.html">Universal Salvage Corporation Essays</a> |</h4></center> <hr noshade><p>Created: 1995, August 1<BR>Revised: 1996, August 2<BR>Version: 002k</p><hr><center><P>This page has been visited</P><IMG SRC="/cgi-bin/Counter.cgi?www.freedom-server.co.uk.Cat-License-or-Death.html" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <P>since 1996, July 28, although The Freedom Server was createdon 1995, August 2.</P><hr noshade><h2>The Universal Salvage Corporation essays</h2></center><hr><p>If you should wish to comment on this essay please send an<a href="mailto:essays@freedom-server.co.uk">E-mail Message</a> toThe Universal Salvage Corporation.</p><hr noshade><center><H3>Cat License or Death</H3><hr><h4>William W. Morgan</h4></center><hr noshade><p>	What sort of Draconian political r&eacute;gime would decreesuch a thing? "Get a cat license or face the possibility of death." Surely this must be a Stalinist dictatorship or some other suchr&eacute;gime?<p>	The truth is, any political r&eacute;gime which wants to requireits citizens to have cat licenses, whether it be one characterized as atotalitarian r&eacute;gime, or a "democratic" r&eacute;gime.<p>	In other to understand the situation it is necessary to understandthe nature of political r&eacute;gimes, and--for the purpose of effectivecommunications--establish some definitions.<p>	First the matter of definitions.  Definitions are required andagreed upon by people so they can understand what each person meanswhen a subject is being discussed.  Without agreed definitions, therecan be no effective discussion and it is not possible to create new anduseful knowledge.  People may agree to a definition only for thefurtherance of the discussion.  They need not accept the definition asbeing final.<p>	Definitions may be already existing or, if new areas of knowledge arebeing explored, they may be created for the purpose of discussion andinvestigation of the subject.  A new definition is, by nature,arbitrary.  If it becomes useful for the purpose of discussion and thecreation of new and useful knowledge, then it become more solidlyestablished.<p>	I ask you to accept the following definitions for the purpose of thisdiscussion.  If you wish to discard them later or continue to use them,that is your decision.  Please remember that I am discussing principlesbased on rationality; emotion should be left out.   Whether thedefinitions have future value for you must be determined by your viewof what happens in the world around you.<p>	After each definition I will discuss it briefly to establish theepistemological thought process  behind the definition, and toanticipate possible reactions and objections.</p><p>Definitions:</p><ul>	<li>Political R&eacute;gime:     		<ul>     		<p>     		<b>A mechanism in which one group of people controls the     		property of all others without their permission</b>.     		</p><p>	In a so-called "<a href="Glossary.html#DEMOC">democracy</a>,"there is implied consent through the process of political <a href="Glossary.html#VOT">voting</a>.  Yetit is highly improbable that all people will agree to all aspects ofall laws or even one law.  Witness the raging debates over abortion,capital punishment, and firearms control.<p>	And the matter of taxation.  There may be vague general agreement byvirtually everyone that taxes are necessary, but near total disagreementon what should or should not be taxed, and how much the tax should be, howthe money should be spent, etc.<p>	Further, political laws and bureaucracies tend to have a lifeof their own.  Once created they are rarely, if  ever, totallyrescinded or eliminated.</p></ul>	<li>A Democracy:	<ul>     		<p>     		<b>A political r&eacute;gime wherein those controlled by the     		r&eacute;gime give their nominal consent to such control</b>.		</p>	</ul>	<li>A Dictatorship:		<ul>     		<p>     		<b>A political r&eacute;gime wherein those controlled by     		the r&eacute;gime need not give their consent to such control</b>.     		</p>     		<p>	It should be seen from the above definitions that there is no	difference in principle between dictatorships and democracies.  They	are both societies based on coercion.	</p></ul>	<li>Law				<ul>		<p>    		<b>A statement by a political r&eacute;gime stating what a    		person may or may not do, and often when and how it must be    		done or not done</b>	<p>	It should also be recognized that all proclamations of a politicalr&eacute;gime, whether they are termed laws, regulations, decrees,executive orders, or by some other term, must be obeyed or the personmust pay the prescribed penalty.<p>	For the purpose of this discussion I will use the word "law" tomean any such statement by a political r&eacute;gime.</ul></ul><p>However, and this is the principle statement of this essay:</p><ul>	<p>	<b>in every political law and under every political	r&eacute;gime--whether a dictatorship or a democracy--there is	an unmentioned concept and associated penalty. This is the fact	that any political law must be obeyed under penalty of death</b>.	</p></ul><p>	To illustrate this, let's take the case of a cat license in,say, the political entity known as "California."  In the "democratic"country of the United States of America, which is thought of as being a"humane" and "free" society.<p>	There are in fact certain local r&eacute;gimes in Californiawhich require that cats have licenses, just as dogs often must do so.<p>	In principle the way the system works in California is that aperson--assuming they had already had a license for their cat--wouldreceive a renewal notice in the post.  And routinely write a check andsend it with the required form. Suppose this time however the cat ownerdecides this is all unnecessary and that the cat--and the owner--do notreally want the license?<p>	After a period of time a relatively polite letter would arrivereminding the owner that perhaps they had forgotten the matter, andwould they please return the form and the associated fee.  When theowner does not comply there will probably be several more letters fromthe "animal regulation bureau," each becoming less polite and moredemanding.<p>	At some point, a letter will be sent indicating that if the owner doesnot comply within a certain number of days they must appear at the"animal regulation facility" to explain why they have failed to comply. And, in this letter or perhaps a following one, there will be anindication that failure to reply will cause the matter to be turnedover to the "court."<p>	When this happens the owner will receive something from thecourt ordering them to appear, explain why they have not paid (althoughthis may not be necessary), to pay the fee and probably a penalty. With the additional note that failure to appear at the appointed timeand place will result in a "bench warrant" being issued for the arrestof the owner.<p>	Issuance of a such an arrest warrant entitles the politicalr&eacute;gime to arrest the individual immediately.  Further, there areno more "niceties" involved.  The individual will go immediately tojail to await the decision of a political judge to decide what to donext.  The person will not be offered any chance to explain and toperhaps recant their sin and pay on the spot, thus avoiding jail.  Thepolitical police have only been empowered to arrest the individual andput them in jail and, according to the system, may not "negotiate" withthe individual.  Only a judge may do this, although it will appear tobe a one-sided "negotiation."  Political judges in almost all politicalr&eacute;gimes are the ultimate source of undisputed and undisputablepower, except by political judges at a higher level.  Except for consummatepoliticians such as a Hitler or Stalin, political judges have powersexceeding those of the ruler of the country.  As Mr. Nixon discovered.  Apolitician worthy of the non-profession would have had the judge(s)removed, incarcerated, or shot, but in a "democracy" they are the ultimatepower.<p>	The political police, normally being quite busy with prostitutes,drug dealers, and other such dangers to society, will not send a SWATteam to your house to arrest you.  However the warrant goes into thecomputer system of the r&eacute;gime and if the individual is stopped for apossible traffic violation or is questioned by the police for someother reason, their name will pop up in the computer.  They will beimmediately handcuffed and taken to jail.  If they are in their car,that will be towed away by the police and impounded.  With "storage"fees probably starting immediately.<p>	Whether they surround your house with a SWAT team or pick you up"accidentally," there are two possibilities.  Either you accept thesituation and go with them or refuse to do so.  Perhaps your cat hastold you it does not want or need the license, and you decide to defendyour friend.<p><a name="1r"></p><p>	The only reason the following scenarios do not happen is because aperson makes a <b>value judgement</b><a href="#1">[1]</a> as to whetherthey wish to pay for their cat license, or risk fine, imprisonment, anddeath.  Death?  Over failure to get a cat license?  Yes, that is thechoice.  Why?<p>	Let's suppose there is a scenario in which you are faced by thepolice, who wish to arrest you.  You do not wish to be arrested, andwill not allow it to happen under any circumstances.  Both you and yourcat see no reason for the license and will not submit.  What willhappen?<p><a name="2r"></p><p>	The political police<a href="#2">[2]</a> must and will useincreasing force to require you to submit to their wishes.  If you useevery means at your disposal to prevent them from taking you to jail,they must use increasing force to make you comply.  At some point theywill begin to understand that nothing short of over-powering force willbe required to make you comply.  Yet you resist this and in theprocess appear to be a threat to the police, since you are making itclear that their escalation of force will be met with escalatingresistance.<p>	Their threats toward you can be perceived as putting your lifein danger, and your resistance appears to put in danger the life of oneor more police personnel.  Since they presumably outnumber you and havegreat means of force at their disposal, the result is a foregoneconclusion.  You will go with them, or you will die resisting them. Itmust and will be this way.  Why?</p><h4>Consider the alternative.</h4><p>	At some point the police realize you and your cat are seriousabout not getting a license.  At this point, the person in charge ofthe police contingent steps back, thinks, and then speaks.  "Why didn'tyou tell us you <b>really</b> did not want a license for your cat?!  Thissheds a new light on things.  If you had told us that before, we wouldnot have had all this trouble.  Please, as long as you feel that way,continue on your way and we shant bother you again."<p>	Anyone who believes this fantasy, please stop believing it,as it puts you in great danger.  And, if it were true, the politicalstate would be in even greater danger.  If no one sees this, they arenot thinking.  What would happen if this were allowed to occur?<p>	You go home and explain this encounter to your neighbors.  Oneof them decides it is not necessary to have a license for their dog. Another, much more brazen individual, decides they do not need a permitfrom some bureaucracy to build their son a tree house in the tree inthe back yard.<p>	Even more daringly, someone decides they do not need a permitto modify their house.  Another person decides they don't need to paytheir property taxes.  A local store, with the approval of the parent,decides to offer a thirteen year old a job cleaning their store room,Or bagging groceries for older and infirm customers.  Another persondecides they will not pay the $1,000 import duty on their car,preferring to spend it with a neighborhood merchant rather than have itbe used to provide guns for friends of the r&eacute;gime to pursue awar with people who are not friends of the r&eacute;gime.<p>	As you probably realize, none of this can be allowed to happen. All political laws of all political r&eacute;gimes, whether democratic ordictatorial (no difference in <b>principle</b> of operation, only in style)<b>must</b> back up their laws by the threat of deadly force.<p>	Again, please do not be confused by the fact that you haven't recentlyread of a battle between police and someone who did not want a catlicense.  The reason of course is that the cat's friend values life andfreedom, and makes a value judgement.  We do this because we knowsubconsciously and implicitly what will happen if we resist.  It willdegrade the quality of your life.<h4>What is the purpose of writing this?</h4><p>	Before we can understand the basic cause of the problems facing thecivilization of man (the specie) on this planet, we must clearlyunderstand the basis principle of operation of our current societalmechanism.  Then, and only then, can we begin to think intelligentlyabout a solution to our societal problems.<p>	The solution will be explained in succeeding articles, but Iwill give you one clue immediately.  The solution does not involvecontesting force with force, nor any means that involve propertyinterference or destruction of any type.  It does not involve marchingor protesting for or against anything.<p>	And, what it does mean, is a solution that is personally profitableto each individual to any of the transactions involved in the process. Itmeans the solution is in greater knowledge of the true problem, so thatthe solution can be understood by the participants.  A solution which,like a raw and uncut diamond, is laying in the pages of history for usto recognize and to implement.  A solution that will increase thequality of life for all.<p>	Contrasted to all the present non-solutions, which bring usonly increased unemployment, disorder, the choice of inflation orrecession, and all the other products of societies based on coercion.<p><hr><h4>End Notes</h4><ol><p><a name="1"><li>All of life requires value judgements, dicriminating	or choosing between possible alternatives. Selecting an alternative	or option which will be most beneficial to you.		<p>	In political societies, as my great and wonderful teacher said, it is	often like choosing between and broken arm or broken.  You would	not voluntarily choose either.  However, in political societies, a	person often has only the option of choosing the least undesirable	option, and not the most desirable option.  Or, more appropriately, of	adding or considering other options.  The political state also limits	your options to those most beneficial to <b>them</b>.	</p>		<a href="#1r">Return</a>	<p><a name="2"><li>That <b>is</b> what they are--political police.  Police	responsible to and working for the political r&eactue;gime.  They do	not work for private organization, thus you cannot engage or dispense	with their services at <b>your</b> discretion.		<a href="#2r">Return</a>	</ol><hr><p>Copyright &copy; 1995--Universal Salvage Corporation</p><HR NOSHADE><CENTER>[<A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>]</CENTER><HR NOSHADE><center><P>&copy; 1995 - The Universal Salvage Corporation</p><I>Specialists in Dying Civilizations</I></center><HR NOSHADE><p>For information on The Freedom Server<sup>&copy;</sup> please contact the <a href="mailto:administrator@freedom-server.co.uk">Administrator</a></p></p><hr><p>The URL of this page is:</p><CENTER>&lt;http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Cat-License-or-Death.html&gt; </CENTER><HR NOSHADE></BODY></HTML>
