<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>MAine Nav</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffcc"><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="rule.2.jpeg" WIDTH="432" HEIGHT="9" ALIGN="BOTTOM"NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"><BR><BR><IMG SRC="maine.jpeg" WIDTH="138" HEIGHT="195" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="5"></CENTER><H1><CENTER>MAINE</CENTER></H1>Maine is a state that has so much to offer to the gay and lesbian community.From the thundering mountains, to the beautiful breaking shoreline, thenature lover will find plenty to fill their days with. If shopping is yourthing, you will have to cut up your credit cards from all the time, andmoney spent at the outlets of Kittery and all of the quaint shops of <A HREF="ogunquit.nav.html">Ogunquit</A>and <A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor469292">Portland</A>, two of many townsthat have a large gay community. If nightlife is your thing check out thescene in <A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor448600">Bangor</A> and <A HREF="ogunquit.nav.html">Ogunquit</A>,you will not be disappointed. However, one of the most special parts ofMaine are the &quot;off the beaten path&quot; places to discover that willmake any time spent in Maine unique! <BR><BR><B><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor442818">Statewide</A></B> <UL>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor442920">AIDS/HIV </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor443079">Helplines </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor445176">Legal </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor445892">Media/Publications </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor446411">Political </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor446889">Resources </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor447042">Support </A></UL><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor447537"><B>AUBURN</B></A> <UL>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor481409">AIDS/HIV </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor447665">Hotlines </A></UL><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor447928"><B>AUGUSTA</B></A> <UL>  <LI><A HREF="me.listing.html#anchor448041">AIDS </A>  <LI><A HREF="me.li