om, we offer elegantly appointeddouble bedded guestrooms with semi-private bathroom facilities. Our privategarden area is the perfect spot to begin the day with a full service breakfastwhile you plan for the day ahead. Located in the center of town we are withineasy walking distance of shops, restaurants, galleries and museums. Townbeaches are within a minute's walk and the Herring Cove Beach shuttle stopsat our door. Provincetown's varied and exciting nightlife can be found,literally , a few blocks in any direction.<BR><BR><B>Elm House</B><BR>9 Johnson St, Provincetown (508) 487-0793 Originally a sea captain's homebuilt in the late 1800's, on a quiet street, 5 minutes from the towns center.Large common rooms with restored antique player piano, sunny patio, morningcoffee, afternoon ice and mixers, parking, a few steps from the beach, biketrails, shops, galleries and restaurants.<BR><BR><B>Flamingo Bay</B><BR>27 Conwell Street, Provincetown, MA 02657, 1-800-flam bay. Newly Redecorated,Jacuzzi, Free Mountain Bike Loaner Ample Free Parking, TV-VCRs, Kitchenettes,Private Baths, A/C some rooms. Airport / Wharf pick-up, 3- Bedroom Apartment.Walk or Bike Everywhere. TAC honored, Brochure Available, Great Off SeasonGroup Packages. <BR><BR><B>HORIZON'S BEACH RESORT</B><BR>PO Box 146, Rt. 6A, North Truro, MA 02652, (508) 487-0042 / 1-800-782-0742.Oceanfront on Cape Cod Bay. 500 foot private beach. Luxurious efficiencyunit, private decks with sliding doors opening to beautiful bay view. 2room cottage with fireplace available. AC, Heat, Color TV. A variety ofaccommodations for every budget. Located between Provincetown and Wellfleet.<BR><B><BR>The John Randall House</B><BR>140 Bradford St. (between Standish and Conwell), Provincetown, MA, (508)487-3533, 1-800-573-6700. Tastefully decorated Inn located one block fromtown center. Both private and shared baths are available. All rooms haveTV, private rooms have VCRs. A large selection of books an